{"TopicId":225203,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"Kopernicus Planet Creator 0.2","CreatedByName":"Draconiator","CreatedById":133772,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-23T05:23:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Draconiator","CreatedById":133772,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-23T05:23:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the longest time I wanted to make something that would ease the creation of planets, and give back to the KSP community in some way.\u00A0 This is not a mod in the traditional sense, but it DOES work with making config files for an existing mod.\u00A0 Anyway...I could not realize this dream for the longest time.\u00A0 I had an idea, but no way to realize it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUntil LLMs like Claude and ChatGPT came along.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used Claude in developing this because their new 3.5 model is quite frankly amazing.\u00A0 So I give you, Kopernicus Planet Creator, written in Python.\u00A0 I got rid of all the bugs I could find with Claude\u0027s help, but right now I need testers.\u00A0 Here is the code so far.\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://app.box.com/s/2xqmghs7my2imepsbelmiyp2hydafjqv\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://app.box.com/s/2xqmghs7my2imepsbelmiyp2hydafjqv\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n0.2 is live, now I have a fully functional atmosphere generator, as well as other minor fixes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dd19453225c9a50759c53702b1df4baf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.72\u0022 height=\u0022621\u0022 width=\u0022799\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/dd19453225c9a50759c53702b1df4baf.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228f86b62d51058935a0d30b9c9e4c5bd8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.40\u0022 height=\u0022628\u0022 width=\u0022801\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/8f86b62d51058935a0d30b9c9e4c5bd8.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002294dfc8e83935c23687412df4dbf31d3e.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002278.73\u0022 height=\u0022633\u0022 width=\u0022804\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/94dfc8e83935c23687412df4dbf31d3e.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022cd89101e2fad96ba1a1f8c41dd39b6d4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002279.07\u0022 height=\u0022627\u0022 width=\u0022793\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/cd89101e2fad96ba1a1f8c41dd39b6d4.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002270c8b41c3f580c23e5e8cd40e4fd16e5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.09\u0022 height=\u0022709\u0022 width=\u0022787\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/70c8b41c3f580c23e5e8cd40e4fd16e5.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fea14384a565442a0c43071757c5230e.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002289.31\u0022 height=\u0022710\u0022 width=\u0022795\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.gyazo.com/fea14384a565442a0c43071757c5230e.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-06-24T04:17:39Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2024 04:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jun 24\u0022\u003EJune 24\u003C/time\u003E by Draconiator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EUpdated\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Infinite Aerospace","CreatedById":230192,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-23T13:22:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, in a hypothetical sense if you wanted to do something like, make a patch to make a JNSQ compatibility patch (2.5x rescale to a specific body), you could do that with this? It\u0027s a really interesting (and useful sounding tool).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-06-23T19:55:09Z\u0022 title=\u002206/23/2024 07:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jun 23\u0022\u003EJune 23\u003C/time\u003E by Infinite Aerospace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Draconiator","CreatedById":133772,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-23T17:08:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure,\u00A0 I just explained my requirements to Claude, and it just coded it.\u00A0 but I wanted to make sure that everything you can do with Kopernicus, you can do here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tangle","CreatedById":66808,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-24T14:19:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224400957\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022225203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221719162488\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133772\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Draconiator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Draconiator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure,\u00A0 I just explained my requirements to Claude, and it just coded it.\u00A0 but I wanted to make sure that everything you can do with Kopernicus, you can do here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI worry that it won\u0027t be as useful a tool as you hope if you don\u0027t have that much of a handle on its capabilities and how it works...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iapetus7342","CreatedById":233205,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-29T17:01:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 title=\u0022Augh, this looks neat\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Y1iF9FhGtcU?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn all seriousness this is an amazing tool that will be useful to future devs! Keep up the work!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iapetus7342","CreatedById":233205,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-03T15:19:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy the way, how do i get a copy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}